Eduvos ITEHA3-T33 Assessment by Otsile Modiselle

This project is a construction of an ecommerce website for merchant SA Online Mart. The client needs to display a range of locally produced artisanl goods for sale with the typical functionalities of such a site. These needs were addressed here through a ASP.NET Core website that pulls and stores data into a database via Entity FrameWork.

Features

Front-End
Homepage: Showcases a list of products.
Product Detail Page: Users can view more information about each product.
Shopping Cart: Allows users to add, remove, and update product quantities.
Checkout Page: Users can complete their purchases.
Admin Panel: Admins can manage products (add, edit, delete).

Back-End
.NET Core Web API: Handles product data, user authentication, and order processing.
CRUD Operations: For managing products in the admin panel.
Endpoints: For browsing products, managing the shopping cart, and completing purchases.
Security & Performance: Best practices followed.
